WEBVTT

00:01.402 --> 00:02.370
HAKEEM: Previously on Empire...

00:02.470 --> 00:03.671
GISELLE:
Her megachurch made an offer

00:03.771 --> 00:04.872
for a Tiana performance.

00:04.972 --> 00:06.507
No! No!

00:06.607 --> 00:09.377
Wait, she is trending
like crazy.

00:09.477 --> 00:11.612
I wanna introduce you
to Kelly Patel.

00:11.712 --> 00:13.013
The king of Silicon Valley.

00:13.114 --> 00:15.083
He needs no introduction
in this house.

00:15.183 --> 00:17.418
I'm stopping the upcoming
release of Treasure's album.

00:17.518 --> 00:20.121
What you did made Empire
look weak.

00:20.221 --> 00:21.389
If I make waves now,
it's gonna look like

00:21.489 --> 00:22.523
I'm challenging Pop.

00:22.623 --> 00:23.557
It's about changing things.

00:23.657 --> 00:24.592
Something has to change.

00:24.692 --> 00:25.759
You gonna come home now?

00:25.859 --> 00:26.794
Ha-ha!

00:26.894 --> 00:28.962
You want me to come home now,
Lucious?

00:29.063 --> 00:31.365
To the empire!

00:32.100 --> 00:33.634
Hey, Yana.

00:36.370 --> 00:38.872
You came all this way
just to slap me?

00:38.972 --> 00:40.274
Don't flatter yourself.

00:40.374 --> 00:41.642
(dramatic music)

00:41.742 --> 00:45.045
I have gigs lined up
the next few weeks here,

00:45.146 --> 00:46.914
but I could not leave
without letting you know

00:47.014 --> 00:48.782
what I thought
about what you did.

00:48.882 --> 00:51.585
You're entitled to that.
And would you get on with it?

00:51.685 --> 00:53.053
I have other things to do.

00:53.154 --> 00:55.956
Every time you open your mouth,

00:56.056 --> 00:58.626
you let me know
how much pain you're in.

00:59.660 --> 01:03.564
It's almost like every person
that you have ever loved

01:03.664 --> 01:05.733
told you that you were garbage.

01:05.833 --> 01:07.335
That sounds familiar.

01:07.435 --> 01:09.137
*

01:09.237 --> 01:10.338
And you believed it,

01:10.438 --> 01:12.673
and I know that's why
you left me.

01:12.773 --> 01:15.576
I left you because
my kingdom needs me.

01:15.676 --> 01:17.845
Does it need you,

01:17.945 --> 01:19.747
or do you need it?

01:19.847 --> 01:21.649
You've said
what you have to say.

01:23.484 --> 01:24.852
Now say good-bye, Yana.

01:24.952 --> 01:31.825
*

01:42.836 --> 01:44.037
(Summer Walker's
"Girls Need Love")

01:44.138 --> 01:47.541
WALKER: * Honestly,
I'm trying to stay focused *

01:47.641 --> 01:48.876
*

01:48.976 --> 01:52.045
* You must think
I've got to be joking *

01:52.146 --> 01:53.181
* Honestly

01:53.281 --> 01:54.215
(Teri sighs)

01:54.315 --> 01:56.217
WALKER:
* I don't think I can wait

01:56.317 --> 01:58.686
* I just need it now

01:58.786 --> 02:01.855
* Better swing my way

02:01.955 --> 02:03.691
(Teri giggles)

02:03.791 --> 02:06.460
Mm, we are gonna miss
mornings like this

02:06.560 --> 02:08.061
when I get back to work.

02:08.162 --> 02:09.863
*

02:09.963 --> 02:11.332
You're going back to work?

02:11.432 --> 02:12.700
(laughs)

02:12.800 --> 02:14.702
Of course I'm going back
to work.

02:14.802 --> 02:16.337
WALKER: * The one, ay

02:16.437 --> 02:18.038
* We could start
with a handshake *

02:18.138 --> 02:19.307
Andre.

02:19.407 --> 02:22.510
*

02:22.610 --> 02:25.379
I have a master's degree
in nursing.

02:26.680 --> 02:28.482
I love my job.

02:29.550 --> 02:30.651
I'm sorry, baby.

02:30.751 --> 02:33.221
It's just, um--I--I didn't know

02:33.321 --> 02:34.755
we'd be having
this conversation so soon.

02:34.855 --> 02:36.257
You know,
Walker's still so little.

02:36.357 --> 02:39.360
I can be a mother
and have a job.

02:39.460 --> 02:42.095
Thank you.
Apology accepted.

02:42.196 --> 02:43.497
WALKER: * I can be real good

02:43.597 --> 02:45.699
I just want you by my side,
Teri.

02:45.799 --> 02:47.435
Mm.

02:47.535 --> 02:49.537
