-LIZZIE: Uh-oh.
-(Janice laughing)

03:49.530 --> 03:51.399
-LIZZIE: Ooh.
-JANICE: Oh!

03:51.499 --> 03:53.467
LIZZIE: That does not look
like a quiet weekend

03:53.567 --> 03:55.068
with the girls to me, Cook.

03:55.168 --> 03:56.770
That's not how my friends and I
wine taste.

03:56.870 --> 03:58.171
-LIZZIE: Oh.
-(both laugh)

03:59.940 --> 04:04.177
Uh, that--that--that was
just a, uh--a misunderstanding.

04:04.278 --> 04:05.479
Oh, was it?
'Cause...

04:05.579 --> 04:07.748
(audience gasping)

04:09.283 --> 04:13.020
Damn, Cookie.
You haven't aged a day.

04:13.120 --> 04:14.655
Looks like bars
can't crack that black.

04:14.755 --> 04:15.856
(laughter, groans)

04:15.956 --> 04:18.258
Upstate is the new Botox.

04:18.359 --> 04:21.595
(laughter)

04:22.696 --> 04:23.831
That's good.

04:23.931 --> 04:25.265
It came to me.
I don't know.

04:25.366 --> 04:28.336
(laughter continues)

04:32.773 --> 04:34.675
(exhales deeply)

04:36.310 --> 04:38.612
You know what?

04:40.981 --> 04:44.852
You and the three brain cells
that you didn't freebase away

04:44.952 --> 04:46.554
must have thought
that was cute, huh?

04:46.654 --> 04:47.721
(chuckles)

04:47.821 --> 04:49.022
I should snatch your ass

04:49.122 --> 04:50.558
and drag you across
this stage

04:50.658 --> 04:53.327
with those dollar-store
extensions.

04:53.427 --> 04:55.195
(audience groans)

04:58.031 --> 04:59.166
(laughs)

04:59.266 --> 05:00.668
But guess what, y'all.

05:00.768 --> 05:02.302
Therapy really works!

05:02.403 --> 05:04.237
-(upbeat music)
-(cheers and applause)

05:04.338 --> 05:06.540
Guys, I am free!

05:06.640 --> 05:08.041
(laughs)

05:08.141 --> 05:09.710
I'm a brand-new woman, honey!

05:09.810 --> 05:11.912
*

05:12.012 --> 05:14.181
It really works, baby,
and that's the tea.

05:15.182 --> 05:16.884
Thank you.
Okay, so which one of you

05:16.984 --> 05:18.486
Jerry Springer wannabes
set that up, huh?

05:18.586 --> 05:20.754
Cookie, the audience loved it.
It was a good laugh.

05:20.854 --> 05:23.924
You're right, because prison
was funny as hell.

05:24.024 --> 05:26.394
You know what would be
even more hilarious?

05:26.494 --> 05:29.497
If I snatched your screaming
newborn from your arms,

05:29.597 --> 05:31.865
handcuffed you, and then took
a picture of your face

05:31.965 --> 05:32.933
as you're about to lose

05:33.033 --> 05:34.935
everything you love
in the world.

05:35.035 --> 05:37.938
Cookie, we're sorry.

05:38.038 --> 05:39.540
How can we make this up to you?

05:40.408 --> 05:42.410
I did a lot of thinking
when I was in Miami,

05:42.510 --> 05:44.678
and I miss music.

05:44.778 --> 05:45.713
Oh, we love that.

05:45.813 --> 05:47.681
We love--we love that journey
for you.

05:47.781 --> 05:48.716
Great, great.

05:48.816 --> 05:52.052
So why don't you give me
a music segment, okay?

05:52.152 --> 05:54.221
Where I make people's
musical dreams come true.

05:54.321 --> 05:55.255
Huh?

05:56.189 --> 05:57.124
What?

05:57.224 --> 05:59.760
-MAN: Um...
-"Um" what?

05:59.860 --> 06:02.463
Lizzie has her comedy corner
where her cronies

06:02.563 --> 06:04.031
allegedly tell jokes.

06:04.131 --> 06:05.533
Yeah, it's good.
It's a good idea.

06:05.633 --> 06:07.701
It's just that our show,
it's not--

06:07.801 --> 06:10.370
The format of Tea Talk
is rage, rinse, repeat.

06:10.471 --> 06:11.405
MAN: Yes.

06:11.505 --> 06:12.440
WOMAN: They say something crazy.

06:12.606 --> 06:14.575
You pretend-threaten to slap
someone's teeth out.

06:14.675 --> 06:17.210
We do it all over again.
Let's just stick to that.

06:17.310 --> 06:18.879
(exhales deeply)

06:18.979 --> 06:20.914
COOKIE: Breathe.
Move.

06:23.083 --> 06:25.819
-Damn, therapy works.
-It really does.

06:27.087 --> 06:30.090
Treasure's album sold
100,000 units

06:30.190 --> 06:31.492
in the very first week.

06:31.592 --> 06:34.962
She is number one
on Billboard, iTunes,

06:35.062 --> 06:38.065
and all ancillary
streaming services.

06:38.165 --> 06:39.467
Great job, everyone.

06:39.567 --> 06:42.135
(cheers and applause)

06:46.440 --> 06:47.407
-Mm-hmm.
-Confirmed?

06:47.508 --> 06:49.142
Yeah.
Mm-hmm.

06:49.242 --> 06:51.278
Do you have something
you wanna add, Andre?

06:53.146 --> 06:54.414
Actually, I do.

06:56.149 --> 06:57.851
Anybody see Billboard
this morning?

06:57.951 --> 07:01.755
And I quote: "A few bops,

07:01.855 --> 07:04.792
"but otherwise a paint
by the numbers Tiana 2.0.

07:04.892 --> 07:08.796
Who cares?
Does Empire have anything new?"

07:09.663 --> 07:12.032
Tiana 2.0 is not something
to applaud.

07:12.132 --> 07:13.967
Our music needs to have
staying power,

07:14.067 --> 07:16.003
and if every record
sounds like the last one,

07:16.103 --> 07:18.171
Treasure's next album
is gonna go wood.

07:18.271 --> 07:19.807
Excuse me, Pop.

07:19.907 --> 07:21.475
(dramatic music)

07:21.575 --> 07:23.310
We need a creative refresh.

07:23.410 --> 07:25.445
That's why I'm introducing
Empire Raw:

07:25.546 --> 07:27.314
a musical event to showcase

07:27.414 --> 07:29.650
our company's new vision
and sound.

07:29.750 --> 07:31.685
So you want to do Unplugged?

07:31.785 --> 07:34.855
Do you also have a time machine
to take us back to 1998?

07:34.955 --> 07:36.223
(laughter)

07:36.323 --> 07:38.058
I'm not talking
about scented candles

07:38.158 --> 07:39.693
and acoustic guitars, Pop.

07:40.661 --> 07:43.463
I'm asking each and every one
of you to dig deep,

07:43.564 --> 07:46.033
expose those parts of yourself
you've always tried to hide.

07:46.133 --> 07:47.968
That's where the power
of our artistry lies.

07:48.068 --> 07:50.638
You do that, I guarantee

07:50.738 --> 07:53.173
I'll win you more ASAs than
Empire's ever received before.

07:53.273 --> 07:56.143
LUCIOUS: Unfortunately,
the ASAs are nominating

07:56.243 --> 07:57.545
in less than two weeks.

07:57.645 --> 07:59.412
So what you're asking
is impossible.

07:59.513 --> 08:01.214
I believe in our team.

08:01.314 --> 08:03.050
We can pull it off.

08:03.150 --> 08:06.754
*

08:06.854 --> 08:09.156
Okay, I'm going to need
to ask everyone

08:09.256 --> 08:11.992
to leave the room for a second
so my son and I can talk.

08:12.092 --> 08:14.261
Stay right where you are.

08:14.361 --> 08:21.234
*

08:22.002 --> 08:24.171
Anything you have to say to me,

08:24.271 --> 08:25.405
say it in front of them.

08:25.505 --> 08:27.107
*

08:27.207 --> 08:29.376
All right.

08:29.476 --> 08:30.878
That's it.

08:30.978 --> 08:32.780
You've screwed up twice.

08:32.880 --> 08:34.715
You've cost us Tiana,

08:34.815 --> 08:37.785
and you almost derailed
Treasure's rollout.

08:37.885 --> 08:39.553
You are out as CEO.

08:39.653 --> 08:42.189
I am retaking the reins.

08:42.289 --> 08:46.126
You don't have the authority
to remove me as CEO.

08:46.226 --> 08:47.561
Empire shares are everywhere,

08:47.661 --> 08:49.730
and you're no longer
the majority owner.

08:49.830 --> 08:52.265
But since
you're a minority stakeholder,

08:52.365 --> 08:53.901
I'm happy to get you a table.

08:54.001 --> 08:58.205
It's VIPs only, but I'm sure
I can pull some strings.

08:58.305 --> 09:00.073
Anything for you, Pop.

09:00.173 --> 09:01.609
(tense music crescendos)

09:01.709 --> 09:04.612
(dramatic hip-hop music)

09:04.712 --> 09:07.114
*

09:09.717 --> 09:11.619
(City Girls' "Act Up")

09:11.719 --> 09:14.121
