12:53.373 --> 12:55.943
* I be with the currency,
I get stacks *

12:56.043 --> 12:57.777
* Bring the cash in, please

12:57.878 --> 13:00.447
* I just wanna live like
Cassius Clay *

13:00.547 --> 13:03.183
* Be the champ,
living so lavishly *

13:03.283 --> 13:05.618
* 'Cause who the hell
wants to be average *

13:05.718 --> 13:08.856
* When you got ingredients
to pass that, that *

13:08.956 --> 13:10.290
(Porsha laughs)

13:10.390 --> 13:11.691
ANDRE: You gonna do
his whole album, Mom?

13:11.791 --> 13:14.694
COOKIE: Sneak up on me again
and that's gonna be your ass.

13:14.794 --> 13:17.831
No, I just got sidetracked
coming up to your office.

13:17.931 --> 13:19.466
I just had to help my baby
bring the heat.

13:19.566 --> 13:21.835
You know that, and that he did.

13:21.935 --> 13:23.803
-Yeah, it was fire, Hakeem.
-Thanks, bro.

13:23.904 --> 13:25.338
That movie soundtrack
gonna be lit.

13:25.438 --> 13:27.007
-Yes, it is, baby...
-Thanks, Mom.

13:27.107 --> 13:28.808
-Thanks to you.
-I gotta get the kids.

13:28.909 --> 13:29.877
COOKIE: Yeah, you did that.

13:29.977 --> 13:31.544
*

13:31.644 --> 13:34.314
Oh, uh, guys, can we have
the room for a second, please?

13:34.414 --> 13:35.815
-Yeah, sure.
-Yeah.

13:35.916 --> 13:37.517
That was great work, though.
It's gonna be a hit.

13:37.617 --> 13:39.086
It's already a hit.

13:40.020 --> 13:40.988
Oh, my goodness.

13:41.088 --> 13:42.255
You and your brothers,

13:42.355 --> 13:43.556
y'all are so talented.

13:43.656 --> 13:45.425
You put me and your father
to shame.

13:45.525 --> 13:46.726
What did you wanna see me
about?

13:46.826 --> 13:49.496
-I have a Lucious problem.
-Here we go.

13:49.596 --> 13:50.763
No, he wants me out as CEO

13:50.864 --> 13:53.066
because I'm trying to let
the artist shine.

13:53.166 --> 13:54.534
No, baby, he wants you out

13:54.634 --> 13:56.536
because your name
ain't Lucious Lyon.

13:56.636 --> 13:59.439
And the better you do,
the more irrelevant he feels.

13:59.539 --> 14:00.941
-It's that simple.
-You still have

14:01.041 --> 14:02.009
your Empire shares, right?

14:02.109 --> 14:03.576
Yeah, I still have
my retirement plan.

14:03.676 --> 14:04.945
Well, use your remaining shares
to back me.

14:05.045 --> 14:06.613
-I need an ally.
-(chuckles)

14:06.713 --> 14:07.780
Baby, I love you,

14:07.881 --> 14:10.117
but I am not interested
in getting in between

14:10.217 --> 14:12.552
a pissing contest
with you and your father.

14:12.652 --> 14:13.954
'Cause it's only gonna
leave me

14:14.054 --> 14:15.222
pissed off and sopping wet.

14:15.322 --> 14:16.256
No, thank you.

14:16.356 --> 14:18.025
Ma, I don't know
what else to do, okay?

14:18.125 --> 14:20.093
If he stops Empire Raw,
then I'm out.

14:20.193 --> 14:21.128
Mm.

14:21.228 --> 14:23.096
What about everybody else,
Andre?

14:23.196 --> 14:24.231
Hmm?

14:25.365 --> 14:27.300
You know what made your father
so successful?

14:27.400 --> 14:28.701
He had a story,

14:28.801 --> 14:31.538
and when he told that story,
people believed in him.

14:31.638 --> 14:33.706
You have a story, baby.

14:33.806 --> 14:35.875
Tell your story.
People will believe you.

14:35.976 --> 14:39.046
I don't know that I have
a story to tell, Ma.

14:39.146 --> 14:40.981
You sure you don't wanna
produce Empire Raw with me?

14:41.081 --> 14:42.082
-Ooh, child.
-We could do something big.

14:42.182 --> 14:43.116
-Oh, oh, no.
-Ma--

14:43.216 --> 14:44.484
No, no, siree, Bob.

14:44.584 --> 14:45.919
I want my music.

14:46.019 --> 14:47.921
I wanna get back into music,
but it can't be with Empire.

14:48.021 --> 14:48.989
Honey, I'm tired.

14:49.089 --> 14:51.291
And that damn Tea Talk,

14:51.391 --> 14:52.592
they shut me down.

14:52.692 --> 14:54.928
All I was asking for
was a three-minute segment

14:55.028 --> 14:56.896
so somebody could doo-wop.

14:56.997 --> 14:58.665
When did a no ever stop you,
Ma?

14:58.765 --> 15:00.968
(sighs)

15:02.469 --> 15:04.571
You just get your story
together.

15:04.671 --> 15:07.574
(dramatic music)

15:07.674 --> 15:09.176
*

15:09.276 --> 15:10.243
(Prince whines)

15:10.343 --> 15:12.512
DEVON: Now there's no more
grapes for me.

15:12.612 --> 15:14.681
Can I have the last one?
(gasps)

15:14.781 --> 15:16.616
-Wow.
-TIANA: Oh.

15:17.951 --> 15:19.286
-DEVON: What's up, 'Keem?
-HAKEEM: What's up, bro?

15:19.386 --> 15:21.021
Glad to see you're back
in town.

15:21.121 --> 15:22.655
I heard the new track.
It's fire.

15:22.755 --> 15:24.191
I helped produce that.

15:24.291 --> 15:25.758
Oh, so you keeping
the Twitter haters

15:25.858 --> 15:26.793
off your back?

15:26.893 --> 15:28.495
(scoffs)
Trying to.

15:28.595 --> 15:31.264
I'm getting through it.
Thanks for asking.

15:31.364 --> 15:33.466
Come on, Prince, Bella,
it's time to go with your dad.

15:33.566 --> 15:35.435
-Come on.
-PRINCE: No!

15:35.535 --> 15:36.603
-TIANA: No?
-DEVON: I'm sorry, little man.

15:36.703 --> 15:38.171
Prince.

15:38.271 --> 15:39.339
TIANA: Come on, Prince,
it's time to go.

15:39.472 --> 15:40.840
DEVON: Go spend some time
with your daddy, all right?

15:40.940 --> 15:42.809
(Prince screaming)

15:42.909 --> 15:43.843
DEVON: Come on, man,

15:43.943 --> 15:45.478
spend a little bit of time
with Daddy, okay?

15:45.578 --> 15:47.614
Come on.
I know. I know. Come on.

15:47.714 --> 15:51.018
PRINCE: No!
No, no, no!

15:51.118 --> 15:54.687
No!
(crying)

15:56.389 --> 15:57.957
-(Prince screeches)
-TIANA: I'm sorry,

15:58.058 --> 15:59.859
they just been really bonding.

15:59.959 --> 16:02.129
Thank you for understanding.

16:02.229 --> 16:04.297
-No!
-No problem.

16:04.397 --> 16:06.166
(Prince crying)

16:06.266 --> 16:08.801
(both exhale)

16:08.901 --> 16:10.537
(elevator dings, opens)

16:10.637 --> 16:12.472
Hi.

16:17.144 --> 16:18.078
-COOKIE: Uh--
-LUCIOUS: Here you come.

16:18.178 --> 16:19.546
Look, man,
I've been trying to call you.

16:19.646 --> 16:20.713
I need to talk to you.

16:20.813 --> 16:21.981
We don't need to talk.

16:22.082 --> 16:24.417
Did Andre tell you
about his half-baked plan?

16:24.517 --> 16:26.253
I think it's a great idea.

16:26.353 --> 16:28.821
What, you mad 'cause you didn't
come up with it, huh, Lucious?

16:28.921 --> 16:30.990
I think you jealous
because you're afraid

16:31.091 --> 16:32.592
he's better than you.

16:32.692 --> 16:35.328
Look, our son is a genius

16:35.428 --> 16:37.330
when it comes
to multiplying money

16:37.430 --> 16:38.865
after we've made it.

16:38.965 --> 16:41.234
-But he's not us, Cookie.
-"We," "us"?

16:41.334 --> 16:42.735
He's never carried out
a creative vision

16:42.835 --> 16:44.504
from start to finish
unless I've laid

16:44.604 --> 16:45.938
the whole thing out for him.

16:46.039 --> 16:47.374
And if you keep pretending

16:47.474 --> 16:48.908
that he can do things
that he can't

16:49.008 --> 16:50.043
and you encourage this,

16:50.143 --> 16:52.245
he's going to ruin our legacy.

16:52.345 --> 16:54.714
"Our" legacy?
(laughs)

16:54.814 --> 16:57.384
He's gonna ruin our leg--
did I hear that right?

16:57.484 --> 16:59.018
Our legacy?
See, 'cause now,

16:59.119 --> 17:01.921
just a week ago,
you was saying how you built

17:02.021 --> 17:04.191
this empire on your own,
and you blew through

17:04.291 --> 17:07.427
my little, measly 400,000
on some bubblegum

17:07.527 --> 17:08.861
and 8-track tapes.

17:08.961 --> 17:12.199
But now you need me,
so it's our legacy, huh?

17:12.299 --> 17:13.733
Well, guess what, Lucious.

17:13.833 --> 17:16.203
My legacy is my boys.

17:16.303 --> 17:18.905
So I'm backing Andre.

17:19.005 --> 17:22.041
Hmm.
"Our legacy."

17:27.414 --> 17:30.150
BECKY: And through there,
a second ladies' room.

17:30.250 --> 17:32.652
You know, Becky, I thought
you were overselling, honey.

17:32.752 --> 17:34.987
You know,
start-ups can be tricky,

17:35.088 --> 17:37.257
and--and they--they don't
last long sometimes.

17:37.357 --> 17:39.326
But you know what?
This feels very special.

17:39.426 --> 17:41.228
You know, Tiana was
touch-and-go there

17:41.328 --> 17:43.596
for a moment, but it turned out
sinning was winning.

17:43.696 --> 17:45.798
So we're doing just fine.

17:45.898 --> 17:49.136
So what do you have planned
for her next after the single?

17:49.236 --> 17:51.104
Well, you know,
we're developing a strategy

17:51.204 --> 17:53.140
that will bring awareness
to her new music

17:53.240 --> 17:55.142
and our roster
at the same time.

17:55.242 --> 17:57.344
It's a slow rollout,
sort of low-budget.

17:57.444 --> 17:58.411
COOKIE: Hmm.

17:58.511 --> 18:00.313
More of a deliberately paced
strategy.

18:00.413 --> 18:03.450
What if I told you
I could shoot Bossy

18:03.550 --> 18:06.753
to the tops of minds
across America in one day?

18:07.787 --> 18:09.322
I thought you were done
with music.

18:09.422 --> 18:10.357
I'll never be done with music,
honey.

18:10.457 --> 18:12.659
It's just, you know,
Empire's--it's got

18:12.759 --> 18:15.362
a lot of baggage, but I love
what you're doing around here.

18:15.462 --> 18:17.530
Yes, sister girls
doing the damn thing,

18:17.630 --> 18:19.098
all by themselves,
no help at all.

18:19.199 --> 18:20.133
I love it.

18:20.233 --> 18:22.034
Okay, so what's the concept?

18:22.135 --> 18:25.972
That's it.
That's the concept.

18:26.072 --> 18:27.039
What do you mean?

18:27.140 --> 18:28.675
Okay, go with me.

18:29.976 --> 18:32.044
-Live music...
-BECKY: Mm-hmm.

18:32.145 --> 18:36.949
New York City girls dipping it,
doing it, day-drinking.

18:37.049 --> 18:39.352
Okay, those are a lot
of my favorite Ds.

18:39.452 --> 18:40.987
Broadcast on live television

18:41.087 --> 18:44.123
and across
every social platform.

18:44.224 --> 18:46.125
-So on Tea Talk?
-Oh, no, no, no, honey.

18:46.226 --> 18:48.027
Bigger than that.

18:48.127 --> 18:50.530
Let me produce this for free,
my treat.

18:50.630 --> 18:52.165
-On me.
-Wha--okay.

18:52.265 --> 18:53.233
We appreciate that,

18:53.333 --> 18:54.634
but what's in it for you,
Cookie?

18:54.734 --> 18:55.835
You know what?

18:55.968 --> 18:58.371
When you guys left Empire,
I was like, "They'll be back."

18:58.471 --> 18:59.872
I am so sorry

18:59.972 --> 19:02.008
for doubting the process,
honey.

19:03.075 --> 19:05.212
I'm gonna help you
get this bitch off the ground.

19:07.214 --> 19:09.182
Uh, well, let's confer.

19:09.282 --> 19:10.350
-GISELLE: Um...
-(stuttering)

19:10.450 --> 19:11.684
-We're in!
-COOKIE: Great.

19:11.784 --> 19:12.819
BECKY: We're in!
GISELLE: We're in!

19:12.919 --> 19:14.554
-BECKY: We're in!
-Great. Let's toast to that.

19:14.654 --> 19:16.423
SINGER: * Some blood pumping,
there ain't no denying *

19:16.523 --> 19:18.057
* I gotta push

19:20.260 --> 19:21.494
TRACY: Hi.

19:21.594 --> 19:23.896
LUCIOUS: Tracy.

19:23.996 --> 19:25.365
Oh.
(laughs)

19:25.465 --> 19:27.567
Thank you.

19:27.667 --> 19:29.101
You look lovely.

19:29.202 --> 19:30.837
Thank you.

19:30.937 --> 19:32.004
(gentle piano music
playing over speakers)

19:32.104 --> 19:34.707
I'm glad we both recognize

19:34.807 --> 19:36.943
we needed to reset
our relationship.

19:37.043 --> 19:39.712
I mean, it's important
that you see me as partner

19:39.812 --> 19:43.550
now that I'm so involved
in the day-to-day at Empire.

19:43.650 --> 19:48.020
Yes, your, um, contributions
have been...unparalleled.

19:48.120 --> 19:49.689
-Ah.
-(both laugh)

19:49.789 --> 19:53.125
And I have to apologize, um,
for not recognizing

19:53.226 --> 19:56.195
your business acumen
earlier on.

19:56.296 --> 19:59.799
I've been underestimated
my entire life, Lucious.

19:59.899 --> 20:03.936
I'd hate to see all of
your hard work be for nothing.

20:04.036 --> 20:05.972
What do you mean?

20:06.072 --> 20:08.275
Well, I'm sure you are aware

20:08.375 --> 20:12.279
of the challenges
that Andre has been facing

20:12.379 --> 20:14.113
as a leader in this position.

20:14.213 --> 20:17.484
I am aware
of the power struggles.

20:17.584 --> 20:20.787
But, Lucious,
you're the only man

20:20.887 --> 20:23.490
who's ever successfully led
the label long-term.

20:23.590 --> 20:26.493
So that means you will
support me?

20:26.593 --> 20:28.595
Of course,

20:28.695 --> 20:30.663
provided you support me

20:30.763 --> 20:32.899
on my latest musical venture.

20:32.999 --> 20:34.734
-But of course.
-Mm-hmm.

20:34.834 --> 20:37.236
*

20:37.337 --> 20:38.905
What if I told you

20:39.005 --> 20:42.108
we were already sitting
on a gold mine?

20:42.208 --> 20:44.076
Now, I have been listening

20:44.176 --> 20:45.612
to some of Philly Street's
new material.

20:45.712 --> 20:47.780
He may have put down the mic,

20:47.880 --> 20:49.516
but he has still got it.

20:49.616 --> 20:52.084
And now he has
a whole new generation

20:52.184 --> 20:55.288
of musicians to influence,
only as a producer.

20:55.388 --> 20:59.359
A comeback record
20 years in the making.

20:59.459 --> 21:00.760
*

21:00.860 --> 21:02.795
There's something to that.

21:02.895 --> 21:05.798
I mean, a lot of the artists
of my generation

21:05.898 --> 21:08.100
are the mega-producers of today.

21:08.200 --> 21:11.471
Isn't it funny how the people
we thought we left in the past

21:11.571 --> 21:13.673
keep coming back to us?

21:13.773 --> 21:17.777
*

21:17.877 --> 21:20.813
(siren wailing distantly)

21:22.114 --> 21:24.951
Oh, um, actually, Andre's,
uh--Andre's actually--

21:25.051 --> 21:26.986
I'm sorry, son,
but you leave me no choice.

21:27.086 --> 21:30.189
I have Tracy Kingsley's proxy,
and with it,

21:30.289 --> 21:32.792
I am taking back control
of Empire.

21:34.126 --> 21:36.162
KELLY: Lucious...

21:36.262 --> 21:37.797
we're all so glad
you're back.

21:37.897 --> 21:39.732
(foreboding music)

21:39.832 --> 21:41.701
You must be incredibly proud
of Andre...

21:43.736 --> 21:47.340
Putting his stamp on Empire
with the Raw event.

21:47.440 --> 21:49.241
Join us, Pop.

21:49.342 --> 21:51.911
I was just updating
our majority shareholder.

21:52.011 --> 21:54.213
KELLY: Andre was taking me
through the program.

21:54.313 --> 21:55.982
-It's ambitious.
-LUCIOUS: An event like this

21:56.082 --> 22:00.420
in two weeks, respectfully,
is reckless.

22:00.520 --> 22:03.423
Though big risks lead
to bigger rewards.

22:03.523 --> 22:05.825
That's what I learned
by watching you, Pop,

22:05.925 --> 22:06.893
back in the day.

22:06.993 --> 22:09.862
I know it's uncomfortable, son,

22:09.962 --> 22:13.400
to have to come and try
and take the reins of Empire.

22:13.500 --> 22:15.034
Well, I think it'd be
truly uncomfortable

22:15.134 --> 22:19.038
for all of us if AUSA Conway
were to become involved.

22:19.138 --> 22:20.607
Well, my name has been cleared.

22:20.707 --> 22:23.543
Well, yes, but public
perception is tricky.

22:23.643 --> 22:25.344
I'd hate to see our team's
hard work squandered

22:25.445 --> 22:26.613
over a misconception.

22:26.713 --> 22:28.515
That's a good point, Andre.

22:28.615 --> 22:30.249
Until the investigation
winds down

22:30.349 --> 22:32.619
and public perception
catches up to your innocence,

22:32.719 --> 22:35.455
I think it's best we stay
the course with leadership.

22:35.555 --> 22:37.056
I think that's wise.

22:37.957 --> 22:39.358
KELLY:
Empire Raw will go forward,

22:39.459 --> 22:42.194
and as far as the matter
of acting CEO,

22:42.294 --> 22:45.264
I'll reserve judgment
until after the event.

22:45.364 --> 22:48.200
*

22:48.300 --> 22:50.770
In the meantime,
let's do everything we can

22:50.870 --> 22:52.472
to ensure its success.

22:52.572 --> 22:57.309
*

23:01.247 --> 23:04.651
(whistle blowing)

23:04.751 --> 23:07.554
Hey, what's up?

23:07.654 --> 23:09.722
Thank you for joining us.

23:09.822 --> 23:11.791
Well, I--I don't have
a lot of time, you know.

23:11.891 --> 23:14.126
Andre wants to go through
a third run-through.

23:15.462 --> 23:18.330
Devon tells me that
rehearsal's been stressful.

23:18.431 --> 23:21.968
Um, Andre's under
a lot of pressure.

23:22.068 --> 23:23.436
Yeah, we probably
should get back in there

23:23.536 --> 23:24.804
before he starts freaking out.

23:24.904 --> 23:25.838
Yeah.

23:25.938 --> 23:28.307
Well, before you do,
I just wanna ask you,

23:28.407 --> 23:31.478
do you think this event
is a--a good idea?

23:32.679 --> 23:35.114
And you can be honest with me.

23:35.214 --> 23:36.583
(dramatic music)

23:36.683 --> 23:39.586
I mean, yeah, Andre
has been calling us in

23:39.686 --> 23:41.921
on every meeting
and blowing up our phones,

23:42.021 --> 23:43.022
and it is a lot,

23:43.122 --> 23:44.957
but at the end of the day,

23:45.057 --> 23:46.493
he's letting us lead.

23:46.593 --> 23:48.928
Well, it's good to be heard,
but...

23:49.028 --> 23:50.463
that's not real support.

23:50.563 --> 23:51.998
When you fell off that stage,

23:52.098 --> 23:55.434
who was there to help you
gain the confidence

23:55.535 --> 23:56.669
to get back on it again?

23:56.769 --> 23:59.205
*

23:59.305 --> 24:00.707
You did, Lucious.

24:00.807 --> 24:03.843
Devon...

24:03.943 --> 24:06.112
who helped you climb
deep into your soul

24:06.212 --> 24:08.447
and find your voice
when no one else could?

24:08.548 --> 24:09.549
DEVON: (sighs)

24:09.649 --> 24:12.685
You, sir.

24:12.785 --> 24:14.787
*

24:14.887 --> 24:16.989
Now, Andre means well,

24:17.089 --> 24:19.492
but the reason
that he forces you

24:19.592 --> 24:21.828
to rely on yourselves
is because he's never

24:21.928 --> 24:24.564
built artists
the way I built you two.

24:24.664 --> 24:27.967
Andre doesn't understand
how very fragile

24:28.067 --> 24:29.802
your artistry is.

24:29.902 --> 24:33.906
And if you recognize
the force that built you

24:34.006 --> 24:37.076
and are loyal to it,

24:37.176 --> 24:40.547
than that loyalty
will be rewarded.

24:40.647 --> 24:43.215
*

24:43.315 --> 24:44.483
(hip-hop music playing)

24:44.584 --> 24:45.885
ANDRE: Ay, yo.
(chuckles)

24:47.319 --> 24:48.588
*

24:48.688 --> 24:49.989
-(music stops)
-All right, brother.

24:50.089 --> 24:51.390
Oh!

24:51.490 --> 24:53.225
Nah, you better support
your artists, bruh.

24:53.325 --> 24:54.994
You remember
back when I was CEO.

24:55.094 --> 24:56.529
Hey, you're the only one
who hasn't blocked that

24:56.629 --> 24:57.897
from memory, Hakeem.

24:57.997 --> 24:59.699
-Come here, boy.
-That's cold.

24:59.799 --> 25:01.167
I appreciate you, man.

25:03.402 --> 25:06.505
